# Battle of Stamford (918)

}}
}}
The Second Battle of Stamford occurred when King Edward assaulted Stamford in late May 918. It soon fell to his army of Wessex. Later that year, Edward built a second burh on the south side of the River Welland. The ramparts of the northern burh may have been approximately 3100&nbsp;ft (c. 750 hides) from Roffe, and the Edwardian burh around 2700&nbsp;ft (c. 650 hides).
